\sin^2(x)-\sin^2(y)=\sin(x-y)\sin(x+y) 
a^2-b^2=(a+b)(a-b)
\sin(x+y)\sin(x-y)=(\sin(x)\cos(y)+\cos(x)\sin(y))(\sin(x)\cos(y)-\cos(x)\sin(y))
=\sin^2(x)\cos^2(y)-\cos^2(x)\sin^2(y)
=\sin^2(x)\cos^2(y)-\sin^2(y)(1-\sin^2(x))
=\sin^2(x)\cos^2(y)-\sin^2(y)+\sin^2(x)sin^2(y)
=\sin^2(x)(\cos^2(y)+\sin^2(y))-\cos^2(y)) 
=\sin^2(x)-\sin^2(y)
\sin(\alpha + \beta) \sin(\alpha - \beta) = \sin^2 \alpha - \sin^2 \beta = \cos^2 \beta - \cos^2 \alpha
\cos(\alpha + \beta) \cos(\alpha - \beta) = \cos^2 \alpha - \sin^2 \beta = \cos^2 \beta - \sin^2 \alpha
